body_html:
Are you installing from source? If so, you need to cd .. or somewhere else.

If not, then it looks like a problem with numpy. stackoverflow says that sudo pip install -U numpy might improve things (upgrade numpy).

body:
Are you installing from source? If so, you need to `cd ..` or somewhere else.

If not, then it looks like a problem with numpy. stackoverflow says that `sudo pip install -U numpy` might improve things (upgrade numpy).
